wikipedia_page.main: (William Francis) Martin Maddan (4 October 1920 – 22 August 1973) was a British Conservative Party politician.  He was elected as Member of Parliament (MP) for Hitchin in the 1955 general election but was defeated in 1964. He returned for Hove at a 1965 by-election, and served until his death at the age of 52 in 1973.
